3E and parts of the atria.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe secondary heart field consists of pharyngeal mesodermal cells that lie lateral to the cardiac crescent. These cells migrate into the developing heart after formation of the initial heart tube. They contribute to the majority of the myocardium of the \u003Cstrong\u003Eoutflow tract, right ventricle, left atria \u003C/strong\u003Eand\u003Cstrong\u003E right atria.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The secondary heart field contributes to the outflow tract, right ventricle, and atria during cardiac development.","The secondary heart field is derived from pharyngeal mesoderm lateral to the cardiac crescent.","The secondary heart field cells migrate into the developing heart tube after initial heart tube formation."],"references":["Sadler TW. Langman\u0027s Medical Embryology: Wolters Kluwer; 2015."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48789"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15957"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48789","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48789"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-20T13:28:55+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-20T13:29:28+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8648"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63338"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clin